fno: Turnover on the National Stock Exchange's futures & options (F&O) segment was Rs 405.97 lakh crore compared with Rs 282.61 lakh crore reported in the previous session. In the cash market, the Nifty 50 shed 5.90 points or 0.03% to settle at 17,610.40. The NSE's India VIX, a gauge of market's expectation of volatility over the near term, dropped 6.24% to 15.73. Adani Ports and Special Economic Zone (APSEZ), Adani Enterprises and State Bank of India (SBI) were the top traded individual stock futures contracts in F&O segment of NSE. The February 2023 F&O contracts will expire on 23 February 2023.
